\begin_layout Subsubsection
Sanity check for the estimators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This document does not provide any theoretical proof of the binned estimators
 for 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(v,\rho,q\right)$
\end_inset

 presented above.
 It is nonetheless possible to check practically that the procedure is coherent.
 Two estimators are provided for 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 that use radically different techniques.
 The first one relies on the average measured speed and the number of traces
 in a bin.
 The other one on actually counting vehicles transiting from a cell to another.
 Verifying that they both give similar results for a given bucket will therefore
 confirm that these estimators for 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 are practically trustworthy.
 It will also certify that the estimation technique for 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 is valid.
